	Random and Exhaustive Generator for Automata
			Library

                        v 1.08.0501

/*-------------------------------------------------------*/


DOC:

http://igm.univ-mlv.fr/~jdavid01/REGAL/index.html


INSTALL:

if you are root:

make install

if you're not:

make install-user


UNINSTALL:

make uninstall

make install-user if you installed REGAL as a simple user


USE REGAL LIBRARY:


use option -lregal with g++


HINT:

If you're already using a package for automata, build a frontage between REGAL's AbstractAutomaton and
your representation.
In any other case, you're free to use REGAL's implementation : DFAAutomaton, or to define your own.

If you want to take a look at an example of how to use REGAL:
make test
source: src/Test.ccp
description: generate randomly 10 complete automata and then 10
automata (without the completeness constraint) of a given size.



